57.4	Heinrich_Schliemann	Heinrich Schliemann	Heinrich Schliemann (German pronunciation: ; (January 6, 1822 â€“ December 26, 1890) was a German businessman and amateur archaeologist, and an advocate of the historical reality of places mentioned in the works of Homer. Schliemann was an archaeological excavator of Troy, along with the Mycenaean sites Mycenae and Tiryns. His work lent weight to the idea that Homer's Iliad and Virgil's Aeneid reflect actual historical events.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/15/Heinrich_Schliemann.jpg/150px-Heinrich_Schliemann.jpg
